2. Perform some common text preprocessing algortihms

- Remove empty reviews. 
- Convert all the reviews to lower case. 
- Remove numbers, tweet account names, website urls, special characters and white spaces.
In [10]:
## Perform some common text preprocessing algortihms

def clean_text(dframe):
    # Drop the rows that do not contain any review
    dframe=dframe.dropna()
    # Convert all the reviews into lower case
    dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda row : row.lower())
    # Remove numbers
    dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda row : re.sub('\d+','',row))
    # Remove tweet account name
    dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda row:re.sub(r'@\w+', '',row))
    # Remove website urls
    dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda row:re.sub(r'http\S+', '',row))
    # Remove special characters
    dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda row:re.sub(r"[^A-Za-z0-9']+", ' ',row))
    # Remove white spaces
    dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda row:re.sub(r'\s+', ' ',row))
    # return dataframe
    return dframe

df_cleaned=clean_text(df_required)

## WordNet Lemmatization (with and without POS tag) 

# Install required files
nltk.download('punkt')
nltk.download('wordnet')

# Initialize WordNet Lemmatizer
lem = WordNetLemmatizer()

# Function to get the POS tag of a word
def get_wordnet_pos(word):
    tag = nltk.pos_tag([word])[0][1][0].upper()
    tag_dict = {"J": wordnet.ADJ, "N": wordnet.NOUN, "V": wordnet.VERB, "R": wordnet.ADV}
    return tag_dict.get(tag, wordnet.NOUN)

# Function to perform the WordNet Lemmatization with POS tag
def lemmatization_without_POS(review):
    return ' '.join([lem.lemmatize(word) for word in nltk.word_tokenize(review)])

# Function to perform the WordNet Lemmatization without POS tag
def lemmatization_with_POS(review):
    return ' '.join([lem.lemmatize(word, get_wordnet_pos(word)) for word in nltk.word_tokenize(review)])

# Function to perform text normalization
def normalize_text(dframe, WordNetLem_Mode):
    if WordNetLem_Mode == "WordNet_POS":
        print("\n-----WordNetLemmatization_with_POS-----")
        dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda x : lemmatization_with_POS(x))
    else:
        print("\n-----WordNetLemmatization_without_POS-----")
        dframe['text']=dframe['text'].apply(lambda x : lemmatization_without_POS(x))
    return dframe

# WordNet Lemmatization with POS tag
df_WordNetLem_POS=normalize_text(df_cleaned, "WordNet_POS")
print(df_WordNetLem_POS.head(5))

# WordNet Lemmatization without POS tag
df_WordNetLem_NoPOS=normalize_text(df_cleaned, "WordNet_NoPOS")
print(df_WordNetLem_POS.head(5))

# Function to perform TF-IDF Vectorizer (inlcuding removing stop words)
def _tfidconverter(_dframe):
    tfidfconverter = TfidfVectorizer(ngram_range=(1,2), stop_words='english')  
    x = tfidfconverter.fit_transform(_dframe['text']).toarray()
    y = _dframe['airline_sentiment'].values
    return x, y

## Initialize the function of plotting the confusion matrix

# Function to plot confusion matrix 
def plot_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, classes, normalize=False, title=None, cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    im = ax.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    ax.figure.colorbar(im, ax=ax)
    ax.set(xticks=np.arange(cm.shape[1]), yticks=np.arange(cm.shape[0]), xticklabels=classes, yticklabels=classes, title=title, ylabel='True label', xlabel='Predicted label')
    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor")
    thresh = cm.max() / 2.0
    for i in range(cm.shape[0]):
        for j in range(cm.shape[1]):
            ax.text(j, i, format(cm[i, j], 'd'),
                    ha="center", va="center",
                    color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")
    fig.tight_layout()
    return ax
In [17]:
## Initialize the function of modelling

# Function for modelling with Random Forest 
def RF_modelling(X, Y, name):
    print("------{}-------".format(name))
    # Train-Test Split with ratio 80%:20%
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state=50)
    # Initialize the classifier 
    text_classifier = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=400,n_jobs=-1,verbose=True)
    # Fit the training data for modelling
    text_classifier.fit(X_train, y_train)
    # Make prediction using testing data
    predictions = text_classifier.predict(X_test)
    # Print the classification Report
    print("Classification Report :\n {}".format(classification_report(y_test,predictions)))
    # Print the Accuracy Score
    print("Model Accuracy: {}".format(accuracy_score(y_test, predictions)))
    # Print the Confusion Matrix
    plot_confusion_matrix(y_test, predictions, classes=['negative','neutral','positive'], title='Confusion Matrix')
    # return accuracy score for later comparison
    return accuracy_score(y_test, predictions)

In [24]:
## Upsample minor classes through Data Augmentation

# Install required file
nltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger')

# Function to upsample the minor classes through data augmentation 
def augment_text(dataframe):
    # Select the targeted columns
    augmented_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['text', 'airline_sentiment'])
    # Initialize the augmentor
    augmentor=nlpaug_augmenter_word.WordNetAug(aug_p=0.5)
    # Initlialize the ratio of upsampling
    aug_sent={'neutral':3, 'positive':4}
    # Perform the upsampling task according to the settings
    for i in range(len(dataframe)):
        current_label=dataframe['airline_sentiment'].iloc[i]
        if current_label in list(aug_sent.keys()):
            current_text=dataframe['text'].iloc[i]
            for j in range(aug_sent[current_label]):
                text = augmentor.augment(current_text)
                label = current_label
                tempdf = pd.DataFrame(list(zip([text], [label])), columns=['text', 'airline_sentiment'])
                augmented_df = augmented_df.append(tempdf)
        else :
                text = dataframe['text'].iloc[i]
                label = current_label
                tempdf = pd.DataFrame(list(zip([text], [label])), columns=['text', 'airline_sentiment'])
                augmented_df = augmented_df.append(tempdf)
    # Return the upsampled dataset
    return augmented_df

## Upsample the dataset
df_Aug=augment_text(df_best_lem_and_stem_dataset)

__Modelling - Different Neural Network Architectures__

In [35]:
## Modelling with different neural network architectures

# Calculate the vocabulary size
vocabulary_size = len(tk.word_counts.keys())+1

# Architecture of self-designed Simple Neural Network
def simple_NN(num_class=3):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Embedding(vocabulary_size, 100, input_length=100))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(num_class, activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    model.summary()
    history=model.fit(X_train,y_train,validation_data=(X_test,y_test),batch_size=32,epochs=10,verbose=True)
    return history, model

# Architecture of self-designed Recurrent Neural Network
def rnn_model(num_class=3):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Embedding(vocabulary_size, 128, input_length=100))
    model.add(LSTM(128))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(num_class, activation='softmax'))
    model.summary()
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    history=model.fit(X_train,y_train,validation_data=(X_test,y_test),batch_size=32,epochs=10,verbose=True)
    return history, model

# Architecture of self-designed Convolutional Neural Network
def cnn_model(num_class=3):   
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Embedding(vocabulary_size, 128, input_length=100))
    model.add(Conv1D(1024, 3, padding='valid', activation='relu', strides=1))
    model.add(GlobalMaxPooling1D())
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(2048, activation='relu'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(num_class, activation='softmax'))
    model.summary()
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
    history=model.fit(X_train,y_train,validation_data=(X_test,y_test),batch_size=32,epochs=10,verbose=True)
    return history, model
